2501.definition: [Ἰωσήφ] of Hebrew origin ({{H3130}}); Joseph, the name of seven Israelites

2502.definition: [Ἰωσίας] of Hebrew origin ({{H2977}}); Josias (i.e. Joshiah), an Israelite

2503.definition: [ἰῶτα] of Hebrew origin (the tenth letter of the Hebrew alphabet); "iota", the name of the eighth letter of the Greek alphabet, put (figuratively) for a very small part of anything

2504.definition: [κἀγώ] from {{G2532}} and {{G1473}};   so also the dative case        κἀμοί,  and accusative case      κἀμέ        and (or also, even, etc.) I, (to) me

2505.definition: [καθά] from {{G2596}} and the neuter plural of {{G3739}}; according to which things, i.e. just as

2507.definition: [καθαιρέω] from {{G2596}} and {{G138}} (including its alternate); to lower (or with violence) demolish (literally or figuratively)

2508.definition: [καθαίρω] from {{G2513}}; to cleanse, i.e. (specially) to prune; figuratively, to expiate

2512.definition: [καθαρισμός] from {{G2511}}; a washing off, i.e. (ceremonially) ablution, (morally) expiation

2513.definition: [καθαρός] of uncertain affinity; clean (literally or figuratively)

2515.definition: [καθέδρα] from {{G2596}} and the same as {{G1476}}; a bench (literally or figuratively)

2516.definition: [καθέζομαι] from {{G2596}} and the base of {{G1476}}; to sit down

2517.definition: [καθεξῆς] from {{G2596}} and {{G1836}}; thereafter, i.e. consecutively; as a noun (by ellipsis of noun) a subsequent person or time

2518.definition: [καθεύδω] from {{G2596}} and εὕδω (to sleep); to lie down to rest, i.e. (by implication) to fall asleep (literally or figuratively)

2519.definition: [καθηγητής] from a compound of {{G2596}} and {{G2233}}; a guide, i.e. (figuratively) a teacher

2520.definition: [καθήκω] from {{G2596}} and {{G2240}}; to reach to, i.e. (neuter of present active participle, figuratively as adjective) becoming

2521.definition: [κάθημαι] from {{G2596}}; and ἧμαι (to sit; akin to the base of {{G1476}}); to sit down; figuratively, to remain, reside

2523.definition: [καθίζω] another (active) form for {{G2516}}; to seat down, i.e. set (figuratively, appoint); intransitively, to sit (down); figuratively, to settle (hover, dwell)

2524.definition: [καθίημι] from {{G2596}}; and ἵημι (to send); to lower

2525.definition: [καθίστημι] from {{G2596}} and {{G2476}}; to place down (permanently), i.e. (figuratively) to designate, constitute, convoy

2526.definition: [καθό] from {{G2596}} and {{G3739}}; according to which thing, i.e. precisely as, in proportion as

2527.definition: [καθόλου] from {{G2596}} and {{G3650}}; on the whole, i.e. entirely

2528.definition: [καθοπλίζω] from {{G2596}}; and {{G3695}}; to equip fully with armor

2529.definition: [καθοράω] from {{G2596}} and {{G3708}}; to behold fully, i.e. (figuratively) distinctly apprehend

2530.definition: [καθότι] from {{G2596}}; and {{G3739}} and {{G5100}}; according to which certain thing, i.e. as far (or inasmuch) as

2531.definition: [καθώς] from {{G2596}} and {{G5613}}; just (or inasmuch) as, that

2532.definition: [καί] apparently, a primary particle, having a copulative and sometimes also a cumulative force; and, also, even, so then, too, etc.; often used in connection (or composition) with other particles or small words

2533.definition: [Καϊάφας] of Chaldee origin; the dell; Caiaphas (i.e. Cajepha), an Israelite

2534.definition: [καίγε] from {{G2532}} and {{G1065}}; and at least (or even, indeed)

2535.definition: [Κάϊν] of Hebrew origin ({{H7014}}); Cain, (i.e. Cajin), the son of Adam

2536.definition: [Καϊνάν] of Hebrew origin ({{H7018}}); Cainan (i.e. Kenan), the name of two patriarchs

2537.definition: [καινός] of uncertain affinity; new (especially in freshness; while {{G3501}} is properly so with respect to age

2539.definition: [καίπερ] from {{G2532}} and {{G4007}}; and indeed, i.e. nevertheless or notwithstanding

2540.definition: [καιρός] of uncertain affinity; an occasion, i.e. set or proper time Compare {{G5550}}.

2541.definition: [Καῖσαρ] of Latin origin; Cæsar, a title of the Roman emperor

2542.definition: [Καισάρεια] from {{G2541}}; Cæsaria, the name of two places in Palestine

2543.definition: [καίτοι] from {{G2532}} and {{G5104}}; and yet, i.e. nevertheless

2544.definition: [καίτοιγε] from {{G2543}} and {{G1065}}; and yet indeed, i.e. although really

2545.definition: [καίω] apparently a primary verb; to set on fire, i.e. kindle or (by implication) consume

2546.definition: [κἀκεῖ] from {{G2532}} and {{G1563}}; likewise in that place

2547.definition: [κἀκεῖθεν] from {{G2532}} and {{G1564}}; likewise from that place (or time)

2549.definition: [κακία] from {{G2556}}; badness, i.e. (subjectively) depravity, or (actively) malignity, or (passively) trouble

2550.definition: [κακοήθεια] from a compound of {{G2556}} and {{G2239}}; bad character, i.e. (specially) mischievousness

2551.definition: [κακολογέω] from a compound of {{G2556}} and {{G3056}}; to revile

2552.definition: [κακοπάθεια] from a compound of {{G2256}} and {{G3806}}; hardship

2553.definition: [κακοπαθέω] from the same as {{G2552}}; to undergo hardship

2554.definition: [κακοποιέω] from {{G2555}}; to be a bad-doer, i.e. (objectively) to injure, or (genitive) to sin

2555.definition: [κακοποιός] from {{G2556}} and {{G4160}}; a bad-doer; (specially), a criminal

2556.definition: [κακός] apparently a primary word; worthless (intrinsically, such; whereas {{G4190}} properly refers to effects), i.e. (subjectively) depraved, or (objectively) injurious

2557.definition: [κακοῦργος] from {{G2556}} and the base of {{G2041}}; a wrong-doer, i.e. criminal

2558.definition: [κακουχέω] from a presumed compound of {{G2556}} and {{G2192}}; to maltreat

2559.definition: [κακόω] from {{G2556}}; to injure; figuratively, to exasperate

2562.definition: [καλάμη] feminine of {{G2563}}; a stalk of grain, i.e. (collectively) stubble

2563.definition: [κάλαμος] of uncertain affinity; a reed (the plant or its stem, or that of a similar plant); by implication, a pen

2564.definition: [καλέω] akin to the base of {{G2753}}; to "call" (properly, aloud, but used in a variety of applications, directly or otherwise)

2565.definition: [καλλιέλαιος] from the base of {{G2566}} and {{G1636}}; a cultivated olive tree, i.e. a domesticated or improved one

2566.definition: [καλλίον] neuter of the (irregular) comparative of {{G2570}}; (adverbially) better than many

2567.definition: [καλοδιδάσκαλος] from {{G2570}} and {{G1320}}; a teacher of the right

2568.definition: [Καλοὶ Λιμένες] plural of {{G2570}} and {{G3040}}; Good Harbors, i.e. Fairhaven, a bay of Crete

2569.definition: [καλοποιέω] from {{G2570}} and {{G4160}}; to do well, i.e. live virtuously

2570.definition: [καλός] of uncertain affinity; properly, beautiful, but chiefly (figuratively) good (literally or morally), i.e. valuable or virtuous (for appearance or use, and thus distinguished from {{G18}}, which is properly intrinsic)

2572.definition: [καλύπτω] akin to {{G2813}} and {{G2928}}; to cover up (literally or figuratively)

2576.definition: [καμμύω] from a compound of {{G2596}} and the base of {{G3466}}; to shut down, i.e. close the eyes

2577.definition: [κάμνω] apparently a primary verb; properly, to toil, i.e. (by implication) to tire (figuratively, faint, sicken)

2578.definition: [κάμπτω] apparently a primary verb; to bend

2580.definition: [Κανᾶ] of Hebrew origin (compare {{H7071}}); Cana, a place in Palestine

2581.definition: [Κανανίτης] of Chaldee origin (compare {{H7067}}); zealous; Cananites, an epithet

2582.definition: [Κανδάκη] of foreign origin; Candacè, an Egyptian queen

2583.definition: [κανών] from κάνη (a straight reed, i.e. rod); a rule ("canon"), i.e. (figuratively) a standard (of faith and practice); by implication, a boundary, i.e. (figuratively) a sphere (of activity)

2584.definition: [Καπερναούμ] of Hebrew origin (probably {{H3723}} and {{H5151}}); Capernaum (i.e. Caphanachum), a place in Palestine

2585.definition: [καπηλεύω] from κάπηλος (a huckster); to retail, i.e. (by implication) to adulterate (figuratively)

2587.definition: [Καππαδοκία] of foreign origin; Cappadocia, a region of Asia Minor

2588.definition: [καρδία] prolonged from a primary κάρ (Latin , "heart"); the heart, i.e. (figuratively) the thoughts or feelings (mind); also (by analogy) the middle

2590.definition: [καρπός] probably from the base of {{G726}}; fruit (as plucked), literally or figuratively

2591.definition: [Κάρπος] perhaps for {{G2590}}; Carpus, probably a Christian

2592.definition: [καρποφορέω] from {{G2593}}; to be fertile (literally or figuratively)

2594.definition: [καρτερέω] from a derivative of {{G2904}} (transposed); to be strong, i.e. (figuratively) steadfast (patient)

2595.definition: [κάρφος] from κάρφω (to wither); a dry twig or straw

2596.definition: [κατά] a primary particle; (prepositionally) down (in place or time), in varied relations (according to the case (genitive, dative or accusative) with which it is joined) In composition it retains many of these applications, and frequently denotes opposition, distribution, or intensity.

2597.definition: [καταβαίνω] from {{G2596}} and the base of {{G939}}; to descend (literally or figuratively)
